{"000-section": {"000-title": "HP Sahara Yojana \u2013 Rs. 2,000 / Month to Poor Patients for Health Treatment"}, "001-section": {"000-title": "Himachal Pradesh govt. starts Sahara Yojana 2019 as announced in HP Budget 2019-20, Rs. 2,000 p.m to patients of EWS category suffering from fatal diseases"}, "002-section": {"000-title": "Sahara Scheme in Himachal Pradesh", "001-normal": "The important features and highlights of this Sahara Scheme in Himachal Pradesh are as follows:-", "002-listElement": "- For medical treatment, govt. will provide Rs. 2,000 per month to EWS category patients.", "003-listElement": "- Serious diseases like paralysis, parkinson, cancer, muscular dystrophy, hemophilia, thalassemia are included. Moreover, chronic renal failure or any other disease which renders a person permanently incapacitated are also included.", "004-listElement": "- The main aims is to assist poor patients suffering from fatal diseases to migrate hardships faced during prolonged treatment.", "005-listElement": "- In the 1st phase, around 6,000 patients would be covered for which Rs. 14.40 crore have been provided.", "006-listElement": "- CM Jai Ram Thakur had announced this Sahara Yojana in 2nd HP Budget for FY 2019-20.", "007-normal": "A campaign would be launched to popularize the Sahara Yojna. The Accredited Social Health Activists (ASHA) and other health workers would identify beneficiaries and will assist them with prescribed formalities. The HP state govt. will also provide an incentive of Rs. 200 to ASHA workers to encourage participation."}, "003-section": {"000-title": "HP Sahara Yojana 2019 Eligibility / Beneficiaries", "001-normal": "All the people who wants to become the HP Sahara Yojana beneficiaries must fulfill the conditions given below:-", "002-listElement": "- He / She must be a resident of Himachal Pradesh.", "003-listElement": "- The candidate must belong to economically weaker section (EWS) category of the society.", "004-listElement": "- The annual income of the candidate, from all sources, must not exceed Rs. 4 lakh p.a.", "005-listElement": "- Candidates must prove their diagnosis.", "006-normal": "In addition to this, there are around 4200 patients suffering from HIV / AIDS, the state govt. has extended their assistance to Rs. 1500 per month.", "007-normal": "Furthermore, the Himachal Pradesh govt. will also start Mobile Diagnostic Van for identification and treatment of breast and survical cancer.", "008-normal": "Source / Reference Link: https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/shimla/himachal-launches-sahara-scheme-for-poor-patients/articleshow/70322269.cms"}}